body:
## Rationale

Six gear category pages are declared in `api/sitemap.js:106-113` at priority 0.9 but have **zero case** in `api/meta/[...path].js`:

| URL | Target query |
|-----|-------------|
| `/gear/cymbals` | "best metal cymbals" |
| `/gear/snares` | "metal snare drums" |
| `/gear/drums` | "metal drum kits" |
| `/gear/pedals` | "metal bass drum pedals" |
| `/gear/sticks` | "metal drumsticks" |
| `/gear/hardware` | "metal drum hardware" |

All 6 currently serve the generic fallback: "MetalForge — Metal Drummer Gear Database". These are standalone browsable pages with real content but invisible to crawlers for category-level queries.

## Fix

**File:** `api/meta/[...path].js`

Add a dynamic handler for `/gear/<category>` — insert BEFORE the default fallback (after the `/gear` hub block):

```js
const GEAR_CATEGORY_META = {
  cymbals: {
    name: 'Metal Cymbals',
    description: 'Cymbals used by 60+ metal legends — Zildjian, Paiste, Meinl, Sabian. Filter by brand, price, and drummer.',
  },
  snares: {
    name: 'Metal Snare Drums',
    description: 'Snare drums used by pro metal drummers. Signature models, custom builds, and budget options — filter by brand and drummer.',
  },
  drums: {
    name: 'Metal Drum Kits',
    description: 'Full drum kits used by legendary metal drummers. Tama, Pearl, DW, Ludwig — filter by brand, genre, and price.',
  },
  pedals: {
    name: 'Metal Bass Drum Pedals',
    description: 'Double bass pedals and single pedals used by metal drummers. Speed plate comparisons, signature models, and pro setups.',
  },
  sticks: {
    name: 'Metal Drumsticks',
    description: 'Drumsticks used by pro metal drummers. Signature models, wood tips, nylon tips — filter by brand and drummer.',
  },
  hardware: {
    name: 'Metal Drum Hardware',
    description: 'Drum hardware used by metal drummers — hi-hat stands, snare stands, bass drum mounts, and rack systems.',
  },
};

const gearCategoryMatch = path.match(/^\/gear\/([a-z-]+)$\/);
if (gearCategoryMatch && !gearCategoryMatch[1].startsWith('item')) {
  const catSlug = gearCategoryMatch[1];
  const catMeta = GEAR_CATEGORY_META[catSlug];
  if (catMeta) {
    return {
      title: `Best ${catMeta.name} for Metal — What the Pros Use | ${SITE_NAME}`,
      description: catMeta.description,
      image: DEFAULT_IMAGE,
      type: 'website',
      url: `${BASE_URL}/gear/${catSlug}`,
    };
  }
}
```

Note: The regex must not match `/gear/item/<slug>` (handled separately by the Product schema flow) — the `!catSlug.startsWith('item')` guard ensures clean fallthrough.

## Quality gate

- 6 pages × 1 meta block each = 6 keyword-matched titles
- All descriptions < 160 chars
- No thin content risk — these are browsable category pages with real gear listings
- Internal links to these pages exist from the /gear hub

## Expected uplift

- Category-intent queries ("best metal cymbals", "metal snare drums") — currently completely invisible
- Each category page links to multiple gear items = improved crawl depth from category hub

## Verify

1. `curl -A "Googlebot" https://metalforge.io/api/meta/gear/cymbals` → title contains "Metal Cymbals"
2. `curl -A "Googlebot" https://metalforge.io/api/meta/gear/drums` → title contains "Metal Drum Kits" (not "Gear Database")
3. `curl -A "Googlebot" https://metalforge.io/api/meta/gear/item/tama-iron-cobra` → falls through to Product/generic (not gear-category handler)
4. All 6 category slugs return non-generic titles
5. No runtime errors from the new object lookup (catMeta undefined check is present)

## Done

- [ ] `GEAR_CATEGORY_META` object added to `api/meta/[...path].js`
- [ ] `gearCategoryMatch` handler added before default fallback
- [ ] All 6 category slugs return keyword-matched meta
